- **Binary Search:** The binary search is used to find the minimum time required to read all tracks. It continues to refine the range `[left, right]` until the smallest \( t \) that ensures all heads can read the specified tracks is found.

This solution ensures optimal performance and guarantees that we find the minimum time required efficiently.

